{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-12645/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-12645"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["1:26:25"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["medium shot"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["low"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["interior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["fixed"]}},{"label":{"none":["Composition"]},"value":{"none":["single shot"]}}],"summary":{"none":["Woman watches seamstresses work"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-12645/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-12645","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-12645/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-12645"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-12645/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-12645/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-12645/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-12645/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-12645/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-12645/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-12645/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-12645/canvas/1/993a2977-3415-4614-bb19-28c87083ee7a","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-30T17:58:53.151Z","creator":"lucia","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>In an interview for <em>Vanity Fair France</em>, PTA brings up Beatrix Potter’s <em>The Tailor of Gloucester</em> while discussing the chaos and late nights involved when making art (Xixax TV, “<a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW156653743 BCX2\" href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sFPecTRpIDM\"><u>PHANTOM THREAD - Paul Thomas Anderson interviewed for Vanity Fair France</u></a>\"). In this children’s book, a group of mice help a tailor complete a dress overnight, all the while trying to keep a hungry cat at bay. PTA also described how the women who were hired to help produce the costumes for <em>Phantom Thread</em>, as well as to portray some of the seamstresses in the film, often stayed up until four in the morning crafting the pieces that would then need to be deconstructed so that they could be rebuilt on camera (Xixax TV, “<a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW156653743 BCX2\" href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zDD_ju7kP4w\"><u>PHANTOM THREAD - Facebook Live Q&amp;A</u></a>”).&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-12645/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:47.53246753246753,120.7792207792208,322.5974025974026,194.02597402597405"}}}]}]}]}